    {
      "id": "readonly-queue-review",
      "title": "Read-only review identifies two behavioral defects",
      "category": "review",
      "passed": true,
      "score": 10,
      "maxScore": 10,
      "latencyMs": 5694,
      "terminal": "completed",
      "reply": "Two concrete behavioral defects:\n\n1. **`drain` processes too many jobs**\n   - Loop condition: `index <= Math.min(limit, queue.length)` iterates `Math.min(limit, queue.length) + 1` times, so it runs one extra job past `limit`.\n   - Also, because `queue[index]` is read after the queue is presumably mutated by `handle`, if the queue is treated as FIFO inside `handle`, the next index may skip the new first item or read an already-removed one. The combination over-pulls one job and may read wrong entries.\n\n2. **`acknowledge` loses work by not awaiting removal**\n   - It calls `store.remove(id)` without `await`/`return` its promise, so a crash or restart before the store actually persists the removal can reprocess the same job. If `store.remove` is async, the acknowledgment is reported as `true` before durability is guaranteed.",
